-- China June Passenger-Car Sales Gains 10.9%, Pace of Growth Slows from May
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-05T01:45:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/china-june-passenger-car-sales-growth-slows-to-10-9-industry-group-says.html

          
          
             Chinaâ€™s  passenger-car sales  growth
slowed in June to 10.9 percent from a year earlier, the  China
Automotive Technology & Research Center  said today.  
 Sales of cars, sport-utility vehicles and multipurpose
vehicles to consumers rose to 839,228 units last month, the
center said. That compares with 34 percent growth in April and
25 percent in May, according to the center.  
 Passenger-car sales in the first-half rose 25.6 percent to
5.42 million units, the center said.  
 Automobile sales in June increased 14 percent to 1.13
million units and gained 30.5 percent in the first-half to 7.19
million units, according to the center.  
